terrapeer.vui.j3dui.feedback
Class SelectManager

java.lang.Object
  terrapeer.vui.j3dui.feedback.FeedbackManager
      terrapeer.vui.j3dui.feedback.SelectManager
All Implemented Interfaces:
InputModifierTarget
public class SelectManager
extends FeedbackManager
implements InputModifierTarget

A manager that oversees select interaction for a group of targets. Management includes checking for multiple triggers on the same target, enforcement of selection limits through automatic de-selection, and notification to collateral event targets of any select events.

In single-selection mode at most one target can be selected at a time. In multi-selection mode selected targets are accumulated. In any mode selecting a target that is already selected de-selects it. The selection mode is controlled via the input modifier event interface and mode flags. If setOnlyManageUser() is enabled system selections are not managed for exclusion.

Target interaction is monitored directly on the multishape target, which means that interaction can originate from any source, even a different manager. See FeedbackManager for details about adding a target for management.

Method Detail

setOnlyManageUser

public void setOnlyManageUser(boolean enable)
If true, only user selections are managed with automatic de-selection. If false, all selections are managed. The default is "true".

Parameters:
enable - Enable state for this mode.

setSingleSelect

public void setSingleSelect(int modifiers)
Sets the modifier flags that enable single-selection. The default is MODIFIER_NONE. Single-selection has precedence over multi-selection.

Parameters:
modifiers - Modifier flags (Input.MODIFIER_???). If MODIFIER_IGNORE single-selection is disabled.

setMultiSelect

public void setMultiSelect(int modifiers)
Sets the modifier flags that enable multi-selection. The default is MODIFIER_CTRL. Single-selection has precedence over multi-selection.

Parameters:
modifiers - Modifier flags (Input.MODIFIER_???). If MODIFIER_IGNORE multi-selection is disabled.
